      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__memory__attr__heap_1ga2a7ef3301abfdd263d86f529dc1ea0f8" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void mem_attr_heap_free</definition>
        <argsstring>(void *block)</argsstring>
        <name>mem_attr_heap_free</name>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>block</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Free the allocated memory. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Used to free the passed block of memory that must be the return value of a previously call to <ref refid="group__memory__attr__heap_1gac03747a12f19735fc1a66d324b19f367" kindref="member">mem_attr_heap_alloc</ref> or <ref refid="group__memory__attr__heap_1ga6ef058b960a23ae8c0e57a71f5518dab" kindref="member">mem_attr_heap_aligned_alloc</ref>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>block</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>block to free, must be a pointer to a block allocated by <ref refid="group__memory__attr__heap_1gac03747a12f19735fc1a66d324b19f367" kindref="member">mem_attr_heap_alloc</ref> or <ref refid="group__memory__attr__heap_1ga6ef058b960a23ae8c0e57a71f5518dab" kindref="member">mem_attr_heap_aligned_alloc</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
